nodes.text: You who are a king over a multitude ought not to be of the same mind as men at large convinced that you do not appraise what things are worthy or what men are wise by the standard of the pleasure they bring you but that you test them in the light of their practical value
You wants to be different from the multitude
The multitude think that you test people and things in the light of their practical value
The multitude is an anti-model for you
